description:
Have you wondered why its important to pray? The trinity? Or how we can differ on politics while still remaining together as a family? This week on ANN InDepth Sam and Jennifer address these topics and more as they try to answer the questions ANN InDepth viewers sent in. 

SHOW NOTES
1:38 - Health Ministries website 
- https://www.healthministries.com/coronavirus/
- https://www.healthministries.com/vaccination-biblical-theological-reflection/
2:35 - COVID19 vaccine and prophecy (Rev 18:33)
4:34 - BRI Article on COVID: https://adventistbiblicalresearch.org/30710/
5:16 - COVID Vaccine and aborted fetal cells
8:16 - Why should we need to pray?
16:26 - Barry Black Episode: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sJz326Tacfc
24:42 - Is betting a sin? 
27:44 - Sabbath / New covenant and Circumcision questions
31:57 - Bible study guides (https://absg.adventist.org/archives -- Quarter 2, 2021)
32:36 - Episode on Sabbath with Frank Hasel: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hwGWE9bSMEY&feature=emb_title
33:21 - Baptism / Rebaptism 
37:31 - Why did/does God reveal Himself to some but not all? 
39:47 - Why did God use the Bible to speak His message? 
42:11 - Christmas and the church
43:09 - EGW and Christmas: https://whiteestate.org/legacy/issues-christmas-html/
45:17 - Should Adventists vote and be involved in politics? 
47:40 - Freedom of speech in the Adventist Church on certain topics.
51:28 - Trinity
53:43 - Divorce
54:20 - Staying strong during trying times
55:03 - Remarriage
55:46 - Dating non-Adventists/non-Believers 
59:53 - Final Question: How can we have differing political opinions and still come together as a family of believers?
